<% content_for :title, "Free Rails Bug Capture Tool" %>
<% content_for :meta_description, "Logister is a free bug capture tool for Ruby on Rails apps. Install the logister-ruby gem and triage issues with grouped errors and request context." %>
<% content_for :canonical_path, root_path %>
<% content_for :og_type, "website" %>
<% content_for :json_ld, json_ld({
  "@context" => "https://schema.org",
  "@type" => "SoftwareApplication",
  "name" => "Logister",
  "applicationCategory" => "DeveloperApplication",
  "operatingSystem" => "Web",
  "description" => "Free bug capture and triage for Ruby on Rails apps via the logister-ruby gem.",
  "url" => "#{request.base_url}#{root_path}",
  "offers" => {
    "@type" => "Offer",
    "price" => "0",
    "priceCurrency" => "USD"
  }
}) %>

<section class="landing-hero card">
  <p class="kicker">Free for use.<br>
  Open source and self-hostable.</p>
  <h1>Catch Rails bugs before your users do.</h1>
  <p class="muted">
    Logister is a free bug capture tool for Ruby on Rails apps. Install the
    <code><a href="https://rubygems.org/gems/logister-ruby" target="_blank">logister-ruby</a></code> gem, send errors in minutes, and triage issues
    with grouped stack traces, request context, and occurrence history.
  </p>
  <div class="landing-cta-row">
    <%= link_to "Get started free", new_user_registration_path, class: "action-link", data: { turbo: false } %>
    <%= link_to "Sign in", new_user_session_path, class: "btn btn-ghost", data: { turbo: false } %>
  </div>
  <p class="muted" style="margin-top: 0.75rem;">
    AI/agent-friendly docs: <a href="/llms.txt"><code>/llms.txt</code></a>
  </p>
</section>

<section class="landing-grid">
  <article class="card">
    <p class="kicker">Step 1</p>
    <h2>Create a project</h2>
    <p class="muted">
      Add your app in Logister and generate an API key.
    </p>
  </article>

  <article class="card">
    <p class="kicker">Step 2</p>
    <h2>Install the gem</h2>
    <pre><code><a href="https://rubygems.org/gems/logister-ruby" target="_blank">gem "logister-ruby"</a></code></pre>
    <p class="muted">
      Auto-capture unhandled exceptions and send custom events when needed.
    </p>
  </article>

  <article class="card">
    <p class="kicker">Step 3</p>
    <h2>Fix faster</h2>
    <p class="muted">
      Group similar errors, inspect request details, and prioritize by recurrence.
    </p>
  </article>
</section>

<section class="card">
  <p class="kicker">Why teams use Logister</p>
  <ul class="landing-bullets">
    <li>Built for Rails workflows and the <code>logister-ruby</code> gem.</li>
    <li>Structured error detail with stacktrace, headers, params, and request IDs.</li>
    <li>Project-level inbox to track unresolved, resolved, ignored, and archived issues.</li>
    <li>Simple setup, no vendor lock-in, and freely available for use.</li>
    <li>Open source repo with self-host docs and Docker support.</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="landing-cta-row">
    <a href="https://github.com/taimoorq/logister" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-ghost">View self-host repo</a>
    <a href="https://github.com/taimoorq/logister-ruby" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-ghost">View gem repo</a>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="card">
  <p class="kicker">Self-host in minutes</p>
  <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/taimoorq/logister.git
cd logister
cp .env.sample .env
bundle install
bin/rails db:prepare
bin/dev</code></pre>
  <p class="muted">
    Full deployment and production setup steps are documented in the project README.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="card">
  <p class="kicker">Self-host stack</p>
  <ul class="landing-bullets">
    <li>Ruby on Rails + Puma web/API app</li>
    <li>PostgreSQL for users, projects, API keys, and events</li>
    <li>Redis for cache and Sidekiq job processing</li>
    <li>Optional ClickHouse for high-scale analytics queries</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section class="card">
  <p class="kicker">What you provide</p>
  <ul class="landing-bullets">
    <li>Required: <code>RAILS_MASTER_KEY</code>, <code>DATABASE_URL</code>, <code>REDIS_URL</code>, <code>LOGISTER_ADMIN_EMAILS</code></li>
    <li>Email: <code>LOGISTER_EMAIL_FROM</code> and optionally <code>SENDGRID_API_KEY</code></li>
    <li>Optional: ClickHouse and Cloudflare Turnstile variables (see README)</li>
  </ul>
</section>
